# 🎬 Movie Recommendation System — Full Architecture

A content-based movie recommendation engine with an **Angular 21** frontend and a **Python / FastAPI** backend powered by **NLP + Cosine Similarity**.

---

## High-Level System Diagram

```mermaid
graph LR
  subgraph Frontend["Frontend · Angular 21 + TailwindCSS v4"]
    UI["MovieSearchComponent"]
    SVC["MovieService (HttpClient)"]
    UI -->|user types movie| SVC
  end

  subgraph Backend["Backend · Python / FastAPI"]
    API["FastAPI Server (Uvicorn)"]
    ML["ML Pipeline (model.py)"]
    DATA["TMDB 5000 Dataset (CSV)"]
    ML -->|reads on startup| DATA
    API -->|calls| ML
  end

  SVC -->|"HTTP GET /recommend?movie_name=..."| API
  API -->|"JSON { recommendations[] }"| SVC
  SVC -->|updates signals| UI
```

---

## 1 · Data Flow (How a Request Travels)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant NG as Angular App
    participant SVC as MovieService
    participant API as FastAPI /recommend
    participant ML as model.recommend()

    U->>NG: Types "Inception" + clicks Recommend
    NG->>SVC: getRecommendations("Inception")
    SVC->>API: GET /recommend?movie_name=Inception
    API->>ML: recommend("Inception")
    ML-->>API: ["Interstellar", "The Dark Knight", ...]
    API-->>SVC: { movie, recommendations[] }
    SVC-->>NG: Observable emits response
    NG-->>U: Renders 5 movie cards
```

---

## 2 · Backend Architecture

### 2.1 File Structure

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| [main.py](file:///d:/Code/Python/MovieRecommendationSystem/Backend/main.py) | FastAPI app, CORS config, 3 API routes |
| [model.py](file:///d:/Code/Python/MovieRecommendationSystem/Backend/model.py) | Data loading, feature engineering, ML pipeline |
| `asset/dataset/` | Two TMDB CSVs (`tmdb_5000_movies.csv`, `tmdb_5000_credits.csv`) |

### 2.2 API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `GET` | `/` | Health check — returns status message |
| `GET` | `/recommend?movie_name=<title>` | Returns 5 similar movies |
| `GET` | `/movies` | Lists all ~4800 movie titles (for autocomplete) |

### 2.3 ML Pipeline (model.py) — Step by Step

The entire pipeline runs **once at server startup** (module-level code), building an in-memory similarity matrix.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["1 · Load CSVs"] --> B["2 · Merge on title"]
    B --> C["3 · Select columns: title, overview, genres, keywords, cast, crew"]
    C --> D["4 · Parse JSON strings (ast.literal_eval)"]
    D --> E["5 · Extract top-3 cast + director only"]
    E --> F["6 · Concatenate all features → 'tages' column"]
    F --> G["7 · Lowercase + Porter Stemming"]
    G --> H["8 · CountVectorizer (top 5000 words, English stopwords removed)"]
    H --> I["9 · Cosine Similarity Matrix (4800 × 4800)"]
    I --> J["10 · recommend(movie) → top-5 similar titles"]
```

**Key details:**

- **Feature engineering**: Genres, keywords, top-3 cast members, and director(s) are extracted from nested JSON strings, spaces removed, then concatenated with the overview into a single `tages` bag-of-words column.
- **NLP processing**: Text is lowercased, then Porter-stemmed (e.g., "loving" → "love") to normalize vocabulary.
- **Vectorization**: `CountVectorizer(max_features=5000, stop_words='english')` converts each movie's tag string into a 5000-dimensional vector.
- **Similarity**: `cosine_similarity()` computes pairwise similarity across all ~4800 movies, producing a dense matrix stored in memory.
- **Recommendation**: Given a movie title, the [recommend()](file:///d:/Code/Python/MovieRecommendationSystem/Backend/model.py#118-128) function looks up its row in the similarity matrix, sorts by descending similarity, and returns the top 5.

### 2.4 How It Runs

```bash
# From /Backend directory
uvicorn main:app --reload    # starts on http://localhost:8000
```

